body: It is one of the oldest streets in Funchal and connects Rua do Comercio or dos Ferreiros with Rua da Alf창ndega. In a session of the Municipal Council on July 6, 1922, it was given the rather vague name of "Rua 17 de Junho de 1922", as this was the date when the daring aviators Gago Coutinho and Sacadura Cabral completed their aerial journey between Lisbon and Rio de Janeiro.
